==Russian==

===Pronunciation===
This letter has no pronunciation of its own. It instead functions as a graphic sign.

===Letter===
{{head|ru|letter|lower case||upper case|Ъ|tr=-}}

# {{Cyrl-def|ru|letter|28|твёрдый знак}}

====Usage notes====
The hard sign has no sound of its own, but modifies that of the preceding consonant by causing it to be pronounced [[unpalatalized]] (i.e. hard). Some writers use an apostrophe instead of {{m|ru||ъ|tr=-}} (e.g. {{m|ru|съезд}} — {{m|ru||с'езд}}) which is considered non-standard or obsolete.
{{pb}}
Before the 1918 spelling reform, {{m|ru||ъ|tr=-}} also appeared after every final consonant (e.g. {{l|ru|грѣхъ||sin, fault}}), or after words like {{l|ru|въ||in, to}} and {{l|ru|съ||with}} that are nowadays spelled as only a single consonant. After the 1918 spelling reform, when the usage of {{m|ru||ъ|tr=-}} was heavily reduced, some typewriters did not have the letter at all, forcing people to use an apostrophe.

